reviewText:
Some of the most charming character design, graphics and music you'll find in the entire indie games market;
Very fun, challenging-but-not-frustrating puzzle-platformer design that keeps you coming back for more without stressing you out;
Overall a very pleasant, satisfying experience with lots of little touches that make this doubtlessly worth owning, especially if you can find it on the cheap.

The downside?
You have to beat THE DEVELOPERS' RECORD TIMES on EVERY STAGE to truly complete the game.  To put it in perspective, on my set of near-perfect runs of all stages I got all of THREE rainbow flowers (signifying you beat a stage faster than the developers).  You need 120 to truly complete the game.  Yeah... no.  *No*.  I'll just take my 110 Gold Flowers and consider this game complete, having had a very enjoyable experience, rather than attempt an undertaking that'd make Golden God on Super Meat Boy look easy, thanks.
